
[1]cruelty

   CRUELTY, n. [L.]

   1. Inhumanity; a savage or barbarous disposition or temper, which is
   gratified in giving unnecessary pain or distress to others; barbarity;
   applied to persons; as the cruelty of savages; the cruelty and envy of
   the people.

   2. Barbarous deed; any act of a human being which inflicts unnecessary
   pain; any act intended to torment, vex or afflict, or which actually
   torments or afflicts, without necessity; wrong; injustice; oppression.

   With force and with cruelty have ye ruled them. Ezekiel 34.
